760 A.2d 271 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND, Petitioner, v. Samuel F. IANNI, Respondent. Misc. AG No. 29,

Sept. Term, 2000.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Oct. 3, 2000.

ORDER

The Court having considered the Joint Petition to Place Respondent on Inactive Status of the Attorney Grievance Commission of Maryland and Samuel F. Ianni in which Respondent agrees to be placed on inactive status by the Court, it is this 3rd day of October, 2000,

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland that the consent petition of Samuel F. Ianni to be placed on inactive status from the practice of law be and it is hereby granted, and it is

ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall remove the name of Samuel F. Ianni from the register of attorneys in this Court until further order of this Court and certify that fact to the trustees of the Clients’ Security Trust Fund and the clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State in accordance with Rule 16-713.
